   Q. Have you given any consideration to the concern about the
so-called sleaze factor and the impact that will have on Mr. Bush's
campaign in the fall (inaudible)?
   A. I don't think that's going to have any impact whatsoever.
   Certainly, there's no basis for any sleaze factor accurately
being portrayed to this administration.
   There have been occasional instances of individuals, but by and
large, I would say that our administration will stand up with any
as far as honesty and integrity, particularly when we have had to
battle so many false allegations by political opponents because we
were doing things different from traditional administrations in
Washington.
   So I don't think that's a factor that should be a bother at all
if people are honest about it.
   And I must say that if you have to look at those kinds of
factors, I think that the other party is certainly as vulnerable,
many more times over than our party ever would be.
   Q. Isn't it entirely possible, though, that you will be leaving
office in late July or early August, not under a criminal
misconduct cloud (inaudible) but perhaps under an ethics cloud?
   A. No, I don't think so.
   As I say, I'll answer any questions anybody has, and I think
I'll be very satisfied with the public view based on all my answers.
   Q. Is there a specific date on which your resignation is
effective?
   A. No, I've just indicated generally when I'm leaving, because
obviously part of it will pertain to the decisions I made as to the
next course of action.
   Q. Will you be returning to California?
   A. Again, there are a lot of decisions to be made, and I haven't
finalized any at this point.
   Yes?
   Q Why are you here? Can you chat about your purpose for being in
California?
   A. Oh, yeah. I'm here _ I was, earlier today, as some of the
people here know, I went up with the campaign against marijuana
planting.
   I have been _ for some time they had asked me to come out and
see that project, so I attended a briefing this morning at the
California Division of Law Enforcement in which that whole plan was
outlined and many of the members of the executive committee of the
program were there.
   And then we went up into the hills, saw an actual plot that had
been raided, and which will be eradicated and destroyed.
   It was mainly to find out about this program in more detail.
   I've been briefed on it each year, but this is the first chance
I've had to get to California.
   I've been to other places before to watch the program there,
talk with the people involved, but this is the first time I've had
a chance to be here in California and observe the program firsthand
here.
   And I'm very pleased with the result.
   It's been an excellent program and a very important one, both
from a domestic and an international standpoint, in terms of our
anti-narcotic program.
   Q. Attorney General, you couldn't be much farther away from
Washington to announce your resignation. Was that planned?
   A. No _
   Q. Was there any specific reason for being this far away from
the capital?
</TEXT>
