detract from your regime?
   A. Well, I think there are many of them.
   I think that during my term as attorney general, we have
certainly enhanced the position and responsibilities of the U.S.
attorneys and improved the capabilities of all of our field forces.
   I think the law enforcement cooperation between federal agencies
and state and local agencies has attained the highest level in the
history of the country.
   I think that what we have done against drugs, the coordination
of the effort against drugs and the cooperation between federal
agencies, as well as their cooperation with state and local
agencies in the drug matter, has never been this high, again, in
the history of the country.
   So all of these are areas.
   There are many more.
   We can go into almost every _ I set something like 25 different
objectives when I started in the attorney general's office, in each
one of those we've made considerable progress or actually
completely achieved the objective.
   OK, thank you.
