<HEAD>Storm Kills 6, Injures 200</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hurricane swept over northwestern
Bangladesh, killing six people, injuring about 200 and battering
villages, police said today.
   The storm hit villages in the Bogra district, 100 miles
northwest of Dhaka, on Tuesday night, police said.
   Abdur Rahman Khan, a local government official, said the
hurricane and four days of heavy rain that preceded it had
extensively damaged rice crops.
   More than 90 people have died in floods and storms in Bangladesh
since the monsoon season started in April.
   Last year, the monsoons claimed more than 1,200 lives.
