<HEAD>State Police Officer Kills Himself After Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state police officer pulled out a
hidden pistol and killed himself as he was being questioned in
connection with an alleged child molestation case, officials said.
   Sacramento County Sheriff's detectives had confiscated Donald
Herman's service pistol and searched him after he was arrested at
the state office building on Tuesday.
   He was arrested for questioning in a child molestation case
involving a 12-year-old girl from Citrus Heights, near Sacremento,
whose mother was an acquaintance of Herman.
   While he was being questioned, Herman shot himself in the head
and died. Herman, 27, of Vallejo, had been a state police officer
for 19 months.
   The second gun was missed during the search, said Curt
Soderlund, special assistant to the director of the state General
Services Administration, which oversees state police. Herman
apparently had the pistol in an ankle holster.
   ``Obviously we're saddened by this occurrence. It's very
unfortunate,'' said Soderlund.
   The suicide is being jointly investigated by Oakland police, the
Sacramento County Sheriff's Department and state police.
