<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Taxi Brawl,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Britons Charged With Disorderly Conduct In Brawl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALMA DE MAJORCA, Balearic Islands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge in this
Mediterranean resort charged five British youths with disorderly
conduct Wednesday in a brawl with a taxi driver who collapsed and
died of a heart attack.
   Witnesses told police the incident occurred July 1 after the
group of youths sprayed beer on passengers in a taxi in Calvia, a
coastal resort on this Spanish island.
   Driver Vega Moreno got out of the car to protest the act, was
struck in the brawl and collapsed on the sidewalk. Moreno, who
suffered from cardiac problems, later died of a heart attack.
   The five are being held without bail in a Palma prison pending
trial, according to Judge Mariano Zaforteza. If covicted, they
could each receive a maximum one year jail sentence, the judge said.
   They were identified as Michael Clark Baird, 21, Adrian
Houseman, 18, Edward Sheffield, 20, Lee Robert Virgo, 19, and Jason
Richard Dunn, 20, all of Bolton, Lancashire.
</TEXT>
