<1ST_LINE>r a PM-FatalFire     07-06 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fatal Fire,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Apartment Fire Kills Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURIEN, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out in a second-floor
apartment this morning, killing five people, including four
children, who were trapped by the flames, fire officials said.
   Dispatch supervisor Lt. Mark Mannard said the fire occurred in
the upper-story of a unit at the La Rochelle Apartments off Pacific
Highway South in this Seattle suburb.
   Firefighters attempted to rescue the five from the three-alarm
blaze to no avail, he said.
   From 40 to 50 firefighters and five engines from five fire
departments responded to the blaze, which took about 50 minutes to
extinguish, he said.
   No injuries to firefighters or residents were reported, he said.
   The fire spread to two other units, which suffered smoke damage.
Total damage was estimated at $200,000 to $250,000, Mannard said.
   Cause of the fire was unknown and the fire marshal was
investigating, Mannard said.
</TEXT>
