<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--BoulderQuake     07-06 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Boulder Quake,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Another Quake Reported in Nevada City</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOULDER CITY, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Residents experienced another in a
series of earthquakes early Wednesday, with the latest jolt
registering 2.7 on the Richter scale.
   There were no reports of injuries or damage after the quake at
12:27 a.m. PDT, and Boulder City police say they received no calls
on the incident.
   Nearly a dozen small earthquakes have been reported in Boulder
City this year.
   John Minsch of the National Earthquake Information Center in
Golden, Colo. said Wednesday's jolt was one of the smaller ones
recorded this year. Some quakes, including one before dawn Monday,
have registered as high as 3.7 on the Richter scale.
   Minsch said he doesn't think the series of small quakes are a
forerunner to a major quake.
   An earthquake of 3.5 on the Richter scale can cause slight
damage in the local area.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
