<HEAD>Fire That Killed Five Ruled Arson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A holiday duplex fire that killed a couple
and their three children has been ruled arson, Fire Chief Charles
J. Bunyan said Wednesday.
   No suspect has been identified in Monday's fire, but Bunyan
said, ``We have eliminated any accidental cause of the fire and we
are now treating the fire as incendiary.''
   He said investigators had traced the origin of the fire to the
enclosed porch of the east duplex destroyed in the fire.
   The victims were Jack Blose, 35; his wife, Deborah, 31; their
12-year-old son, Jack Jr.; 5-year-old daughter, Rachel; and
4-year-old daughter, Lacey.
   Karen Campbell, who lived in the other half of the duplex, was
out of town and returned to find the building in ruins.
   Bunyan said investigators had interviewed both Mrs. Campbell and
the landlord, Herbert Klebaum Jr.

