   The museum will house 25 restored cars from the 1940s, 1950s and
1960s, plus personal items and career mementoes, she said.
   Williams, who lives in this northwestern Tennessee city, is the
reigning Country Music Association entertainer of the year. His
hits include ``All My Rowdy Friends'' and ``Family Tradition.''
