<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An air force Mirage jet fighter jet
crashed into a two-story food processing plant Wednesday, killing
both crewmen and 13 plant workers, authorities reported.
   The crash injured 32 workers and started a fire that severely
damaged the factory, according to company officials, rescue workers
and witnesses.
   A witness, Bashir Baloch, said the fighter was burning when it
hit the building. The plant processes cooking oil and other foods,
employing about 200 people.
