<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     07-06 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stock Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were broadly higher Wednesday,
boosted mainly by Wall Street's better-than-expected performance
Tuesday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was up 13.1
points, or 0.1 percent, at 1,867.9 at midday. Volume totaled a
light 267.8 million shares.
   Shares were boosted by the positive overnight performance of the
New York and Tokyo markets, and oil stocks were among the best
performers.
   But dealers said fund managers in London steered clear of
significant involvement in equity trading amid perceptions that the
London market lacks the impetus to move sharply up or down in the
near term.
   On Tuesday, London players harbored fears that Wall Street might
drop after an Iranian commercial airliner was downed by the U.S.
Navy.
   But the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials gained 27.03 points
to finish at 2,158.61.
</TEXT>
