<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Finish Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices finished higher Wednesday after a
late afternoon surge in reaction to Wall Street's early rise.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 15.2
points, or 0.8 percent, to 1,870.0.
   The closing level was fractionally below the day's high of
1,870.2.
   Volume was 500.2 million shares, up from Tuesday's 383.2 million.
   Traders said the index moved in positive territory throughout
the morning, fell back to its lowest point of 1,863.2 by early
afternoon, and resumed its upward drive late in the session.
   By the close of London's business day, the Dow Jones Industrial
Average was up 4.98 points at 2,163.58. Traders said they were
heartened by Wall Street's ability to overcome some opening
weakness.
   ``We had a lull after lunch as Wall Street was wobbling
around,'' said one London equity salesman, adding that ``as soon as
New York gained its footing, London was keen to go higher.''
</TEXT>
