<TEXT>
   A late wave of selling sent stock prices
tumbling today, reversing the advance that carried the market to
new highs for the year on Tuesday.
   Analysts attributed the drop to selling by professionals engaged
in computer-program trading strategies involving stock-index
futures and ``baskets'' of individual stocks.
   ``The last half hour was all programs,'' said Newton Zinder at
