<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A late wave of selling drove stock prices lower
Wednesday, reversing the advance that carried the market to new
1988 highs the day before.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up 27.03 on Tuesday,
fell back 28.45 to 2,130.16.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by more than 9 to 5 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
515 up, 976 down and 466 unchanged.
